revision.text:
'''Bindoo wind farm''' is a [[Wind turbine|wind farm]] located close to [[Cootehill]], [[Cavan]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] and erected in 2007. The farm was built and is run by [[Airtricity]]. The wind farm has 32 [[GE 1.5 MW Wind Turbine]]s with a 65-metre hub height and 70 metre rotor diameter giving a total capacity of 48 megawatts. As of June 2007 it is the second largest wind farm (by power generated) in Ireland.<ref>[http://www.enviroireland.com/detail.asp?item=1862 Airtricity Opens 48MW Bindoo Wind Farm]{{dead link|date=June 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.airtricity.com/ireland/media_center/press_releases/ireland/Bindoo%20opening.pdf Airtricity opens 48MW Bindoo wind farm in Co. Cavan]</ref>

