{{Infobox park | name = Ngong Forest | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | map = Kenya | map_width = | type = | location = Ngong Road, [[Nairobi]], Kenya | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{Coord|1|18|59.12|S|36|44|30.13|E|display=inline,title}} | area = 1224 hectares | created = | operator = Ngong Road Forest Sanctuaries | visitation_num = | status = | designation = | open = }} '''Ngong Forest''' is one of the few natural forests in a capital city of Kenya. Located {{convert|6|km|mile}} from the central business district of [[Nairobi]], the Ngong Forest is in [[Ngong Hills]] along [[Ngong Road]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://softkenya.com/kenya/ngong-forest/|title=Ngong Forest|date=2011-08-24|work=Softkenya.com|access-date=2017-05-10|language=en-US}}</ref> Managed by the Ngong Road Forest Sanctuaries,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.victoriasafaris.com/kenya/excursions.html|title=Ngong Forest Walks, Ngong Forest Tours, Excursions in Ngong Forest, Nairobi Tours, Nairobi Safdari Walk, Nairobi Orphanage, Nairobi Charity Tours, Kibera Slum Tours, Kibera Charity Tours, Kibera Pro Poor Tours|website=www.victoriasafaris.com|access-date=2017-05-10}}</ref> this habitat of indigenous trees is home to many wild animals, including leopards, [[spotted hyena]]s, and [[Cape bushbuck]]s. Other animal residents include [[crowned eagle]]s, owls, snakes, and many other birds and reptiles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://runningwild.co.ke/running-wild-road-map/ngong-forest-sanctuary|title=Hidden Tranquility at the Ngong Forest Sanctuary - Running Wild|date=2015-11-29|work=Running Wild|access-date=2017-05-10|language=en-US}}</ref>
Ngong Forest, which extends to [[Rift Valley Province]], has undergone [[deforestation]] due to the settlement of [[Karen, Kenya|Karen]] and [[Ngong, Kenya|Ngong]], as well as to the development of the [[Lenana School]] and the [[Ngong Racecourse]]. These events have reduced Ngong Forest's original {{Convert|2926.6|ha}} to the current {{Convert|1224|ha}}.
