'''Odigha Odigha''' is a Nigerian educator, environmentalist and activist. He was awarded  the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2003, for his efforts on protection of the rainforests of [[Cross River State]] from industrial logging.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/149  |title=Africa 2003. Odigha Odigha. Nigeria, Forests |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=18 November 2010}}</ref>

