[[File:Blick vom aussichtsturm hörlitz4.jpg|thumb|Part of the Solarpark; north of Hörlitz]]
The '''Senftenberg Solarpark''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] located on former open-pit mining areas close to the city of [[Senftenberg]], in [[Eastern Germany]]. The 78 MW Phase 1 of the plant was completed within three months and generates power for about 25,000 households. It was opened on September 24, 2011, by the Prime Minister of the German state of Brandenburg. The ground-based PV plant is designed for a total capacity of 148 MW.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.solarserver.com/solar-magazine/solar-news/current/2011/kw39/78-mw-of-the-worlds-largest-solar-photovoltaic-plant-connected-to-grid-in-senftenberg-germany.html |title=78 MW of the world's largest solar photovoltaic plant connected to grid in Senftenberg, Germany |author= |date=2011-09-28 |work=Solar Server }}</ref>

[https://web.archive.org/web/20140322013828/http://www.lmbv.de/index.php/solarpark-senftenberg.html Solarpark Senftenberg/Schipkau]

